		<p>Sorry for the late response, Ryan. I somehow missed your question. All of those chilies should already be dried when you purchase them, so you&#8217;re not really cooking raw peppers. You&#8217;re only putting them in the oven to toast them, which should not present the problems you&#8217;ve previously experienced. </p>
<p>Matt, the rules were gathered from various chefs participating in the competition. Some people put beans in their chili and others don&#8217;t. It just so happens that Northern Spy Food Co.&#8217;s chili didn&#8217;t have beans.</p>

